## 3. Empty State Design

### 3.1 No Chat Selected Component
**File: `src/components/NoChatSelected.jsx`**

**Key Concepts:**
- Empty state user experience
- Centered content layout
- Animation for engagement
- Clear instructional messaging

**Code Analysis:**
```jsx
// File: src/components/NoChatSelected.jsx
import { MessageSquare } from "lucide-react";

const NoChatSelected = () => {
  return (
    <div className="w-full flex flex-1 flex-col items-center justify-center p-16 bg-base-100/50">
      <div className="max-w-md text-center space-y-6">
        {/* Animated Icon Display */}
        <div className="flex justify-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div className="relative">
            <div className="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center
                          justify-center animate-bounce">
              <MessageSquare className="w-8 h-8 text-primary" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Welcome Content */}
        <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold">Welcome to Chatty!</h2>
        <p className="text-base-content/60">
          Select a conversation from the sidebar to start chatting
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

**Learning Points:**
