## 5. Responsive Design Patterns

### 5.1 Mobile-First Approach

**Sidebar Responsiveness:**
```jsx
// Adaptive width
className="h-full w-20 lg:w-72"

// Conditional text display
<span className="font-medium hidden lg:block">Contacts</span>

// Responsive positioning
<div className="relative mx-auto lg:mx-0">

// Hidden elements on mobile
<div className="mt-3 hidden lg:flex items-center gap-2">
```

**Navigation Responsiveness:**
```jsx
// Hidden text on small screens
<span className="hidden sm:inline">Settings</span>
<span className="hidden sm:inline">Profile</span>
<span className="hidden sm:inline">Logout</span>
```

**Grid Responsiveness:**
```jsx
// Responsive grid columns
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 sm:grid-cols-6 md:grid-cols-8 gap-2">
```

### 5.2 CSS Utility Patterns

**Flexbox Layouts:**
```jsx
"flex items-center justify-between"
"flex items-center gap-3"
"flex flex-col items-center gap-1.5"
```

**Spacing and Sizing:**
```jsx
"size-9" // width and height
"gap-2.5" // gap between elements
"p-16" // padding
"space-y-6" // vertical spacing between children
```

**Visual Effects:**
```jsx
"backdrop-blur-lg" // glass effect
"bg-base-100/80" // opacity modifier
"animate-bounce" // animation
"transition-all" // smooth transitions
```

